{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":116289,"duration_api_ms":181329,"num_turns":5,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a0cad288-4b65-49cf-9272-6c930a7e7ddc","total_cost_usd":0.5104143999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":1644,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29174,"cache_read_input_tokens":80761,"output_tokens":3095,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":29174,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":202,"outputTokens":12389,"cacheReadInputTokens":793844,"cacheCreationInputTokens":48456,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.20210140000000004,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":1644,"outputTokens":3095,"cacheReadInputTokens":80761,"cacheCreationInputTokens":29174,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.308313,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All five amendments identify verified defects introduced by the retry/backoff changes. Code inspection confirms: (1) four resume tests use with_transient_failure(stage, 3) against a max_attempts of 5, (2) those same tests lack start_paused=true unlike peer retry tests, (3) BackendUnavailable from the availability path maps to retryable TransportFailure while BinaryNotFound (terminal) only fires on rarer spawn/exit-code paths, (4) tokio::time::sleep(backoff) at engine.rs:4637 has no cancellation awareness creating a TOCTOU window, and (5) timeout errors route through cleanup() which deletes artifacts instead of cleanup_failed_invocation() which preserves them.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-1-2fc8a73c","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: all four resume tests (lines 1043, 1111, 1417, 3037) use with_transient_failure(stage, 3) while retry_policy.rs:45 sets TransportFailure max_attempts to 5. With only 3 injected failures the 4th attempt succeeds within budget, breaking assert!(first_result.is_err()). The retry_exhaustion test at line 2718 already uses count=5 as the correct pattern. Bumping to 5 is the minimal correct fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-171fc893","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: all four resume tests use plain #[tokio::test] while peer retry tests (retry_exhaustion at line 2709, cancellation_halts at line 3768, cancellation_between at line 3816) already use #[tokio::test(start_paused = true)]. With exponential backoff (5s+10s+20s per retry cycle), each test would add ~35s of real wall-clock delay. Adding start_paused=true makes tokio::time::sleep advance instantly, consistent with the existing pattern in the file."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-5008e57c","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: resolve_binary() (line 493), ensure_binary_available() (lines 883-895), and check_availability() (lines 1121-1132) all return AppError::BackendUnavailable for missing binaries. error.rs:302 maps BackendUnavailable to FailureClass::TransportFailure (retryable, 5 attempts). BinaryNotFound (terminal per retry_policy.rs:57) is only reached via the rarer spawn-NotFound path (line 937) or exit-code-127 path (line 1383). The common case of a missing claude/codex binary burns all 5 retries before failing, defeating the fast-fail intent. The availability/build-command path must emit BinaryNotFound directly."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-06c34f70","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: engine.rs:4637 performs a plain tokio::time::sleep(backoff).await. The cancellation check at line 4561 gates will_retry, but cancellation arriving after that check and during the sleep (which can last up to 60s per the backoff calculation) creates a TOCTOU window where the run sits idle instead of shutting down promptly. No tokio::select! is used anywhere in engine.rs. The standard fix of racing the sleep against cancellation_token.cancelled() via tokio::select! is correct and necessary for responsive shutdown."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-8b4ded53","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: timeout errors from spawn_and_wait() (lines 987-1001) flow to invoke()'s catch-all at lines 1161-1163 which calls prepared.cleanup(). For Codex backends, cleanup() (lines 55-63) calls best_effort_cleanup() which deletes temp files. In contrast, cleanup_failed_invocation() (lines 66-90) preserves artifacts by moving them to runtime/failed/. A timeout (hung backend) produces less diagnostic evidence than a normal non-zero exit, which is backwards — timeout failures are arguably more worth inspecting. The timeout path should route through the preserving cleanup."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"f37f7cb5-a945-4c2a-ac85-de9a65442803"}
